## 1. Frontend — HTML

### Reduce Initial Page Load

- **Defer non-critical scripts** — Use `defer` or `async` so HTML parsing isn't blocked
  ```html
  <script src="app.js" defer></script>
  ```
  - `defer` — executes after HTML fully parsed, in order
  - `async` — executes as soon as downloaded, order not guaranteed (use for independent scripts like analytics)

- **Preload critical assets** — Fonts, hero images, critical CSS fetched early in parallel
  ```html
  <link rel="preload" href="hero.webp" as="image" />
  <link rel="preload" href="font.woff2" as="font" crossorigin />
  ```

- **Prefetch next-page resources** — Browser fetches in idle time for likely next navigation
  ```html
  <link rel="prefetch" href="/dashboard" />
  ```

- **Preconnect to third-party origins** — Reduces DNS lookup + TLS handshake time upfront
  ```html
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  ```

