## 2. Frontend — CSS

### Reflow vs Repaint — understand this first

```
Property changes          → What browser does         → Cost
width/height/margin       → Reflow + Repaint           → Most expensive
color/background          → Repaint only               → Medium
transform/opacity         → Compositor only (GPU)      → Cheapest — use for animations
```

- **Avoid layout thrashing** — Reading layout property after writing forces reflow
  ```css
  /* BAD — triggers reflow on every frame */
  .box { left: 100px; }

  /* GOOD — compositor-only, no reflow */
  .box { transform: translateX(100px); }
  ```

- **Use `will-change` sparingly** — Promotes element to its own GPU layer
  ```css
  .animated-card { will-change: transform; }
  ```
  > Only add when you actually have animation. Every GPU layer consumes memory. Don't put on every element.

- **CSS containment** — Tells browser: "changes inside this box don't affect anything outside"
  ```css
  .card { contain: layout style paint; }
  ```
  Useful for widget-style components, dashboards, cards — prevents layout changes from bubbling up.

### Reduce CSS File Size

- **PurgeCSS** — Scans your HTML/JSX and removes CSS selectors that don't appear in your templates
  - What it is: A build tool / PostCSS plugin
  - When useful: Most powerful with utility frameworks like Bootstrap or Tailwind — removes 90%+ of shipped CSS that no component actually uses
  - Result: A 300KB stylesheet can shrink to 8KB after purging

- Minify CSS in production — Vite/Webpack do this automatically
- Split CSS per route — don't load dashboard styles on the landing page

### Fonts

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'Inter';
  src: url('inter.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-display: swap; /* show fallback text immediately — don't block rendering */
}
```

- Without `font-display: swap`: text is invisible until font loads (FOIT — Flash of Invisible Text)
- With `swap`: system font shows immediately, custom font replaces it (FOUT — acceptable trade-off)
- Subset fonts — full font file is 500KB+, a Latin subset is ~20KB
- Prefer system fonts for body text where branding allows — zero download cost

### Animation Performance

- Only animate `transform` and `opacity` — GPU-accelerated, no layout recalculation
- Always add reduced motion support:
  ```css
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * { animation: none !important; transition: none !important; }
  }
  ```

