### Avoid Blocking the Main Thread

- Move heavy computation to **Web Workers** — runs in a separate thread, never blocks UI
  ```js
  const worker = new Worker('heavy-task.js');
  worker.postMessage(largeDataset);
  worker.onmessage = (e) => setResults(e.data);
  ```
- Break long tasks with `setTimeout(fn, 0)` or `scheduler.postTask()`
- Use `requestIdleCallback` for non-urgent background work

### Memory Management

- Remove event listeners on cleanup — memory leak #1 source
- Clear `setInterval` / `setTimeout` on unmount
- Avoid closures that unintentionally keep large objects in scope

### Bundle Analysis Tools

| Tool | What it is | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| **webpack-bundle-analyzer** | Visual treemap — every module shown by size | Bundle is too large and you don't know why |
| **rollup-plugin-visualizer** | Same but for Vite/Rollup | Vite projects |
| **source-map-explorer** | Shows exact module sizes from source maps | Debugging specific chunk sizes |
| **Bundlephobia** (bundlephobia.com) | Shows npm package size + tree-shaking potential | Before installing a new dependency |

