## 4. Frontend — React

### 4.1 General React Performance

- **Avoid unnecessary re-renders** — the #1 React performance issue
- React re-renders when: state changes, props change, parent re-renders, context value changes
- A component re-rendering does NOT always update the DOM — React diffs first. But excessive render function execution is still wasted CPU.

### 4.2 Component Performance

**`React.memo`** — Skip re-render if props haven't changed (shallow comparison)
```jsx
const UserCard = React.memo(({ name, email }) => {
  return <div>{name} — {email}</div>;
});
// Re-renders only when `name` or `email` changes
// WITHOUT memo: re-renders every time the parent renders, even if props are same
```

> Caveat: If you pass an object/array as a prop — `{}` !== `{}` in JS — memo won't help. Memoize the prop too.

**`useMemo`** — Memoize expensive computed values
```jsx
// WITHOUT useMemo: sort runs on every render
const sorted = items.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));

// WITH useMemo: sort only runs when `items` changes
const sorted = useMemo(() => {
  return [...items].sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));
}, [items]);
```

**`useCallback`** — Stable function reference so React.memo child doesn't re-render
```jsx
// WITHOUT: new function reference on every render → child always re-renders
const handleDelete = () => dispatch(deleteItem(id));

// WITH: same reference unless `id` changes → child skips render
const handleDelete = useCallback(() => {
  dispatch(deleteItem(id));
}, [id]);
```

**`useTransition`** (React 18) — Mark state updates as non-urgent so input stays responsive
```jsx
const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
const [results, setResults] = useState(data);
const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

function handleSearch(e) {
  setQuery(e.target.value);           // urgent — update input field immediately
  startTransition(() => {
    setResults(filter(data, e.target.value)); // non-urgent — can wait
  });
}
// Input field updates instantly; list filtering happens without blocking the input
```

**`useDeferredValue`** (React 18) — Defer rendering of a slow subtree
```jsx
const deferredQuery = useDeferredValue(searchQuery);
// Pass deferredQuery (not searchQuery) to the expensive list component
// List renders with slight delay while input stays responsive
```

