### 4.4 Identifying Large / Slow Components

**Code symptoms:**
- Component file is 300+ lines — almost always doing too many things
- More than 4–5 `useState` hooks — state management is mixed with UI rendering
- Component fetches data AND renders it AND handles business logic all in one
- Input typing feels laggy — input state is held too high in the tree causing full subtree re-render
- Entire page re-renders when only a small widget changes

**DevTools symptoms:**
- Component appears at top of Ranked chart in Profiler
- Component renders on every keystroke when it shouldn't
- Context consumer re-renders even when the value it uses didn't change

---

### 4.5 How to Fix Large / Slow Components

**Split by responsibility (Single Responsibility Principle):**

```
Before: <ProductPage />
  — fetches data
  — manages filter state
  — manages sort state
  — renders 500 rows
  — handles pagination
  → One filter change re-renders the entire page

After:
  <ProductPage />        ← layout only, coordinates children
    <ProductFilters />   ← owns filter state only
    <ProductTable />     ← receives data via props, renders rows
    <Pagination />       ← owns page number state only
  → Filter change re-renders only <ProductFilters /> and <ProductTable />
```

**Lift state down:**

```jsx
// BAD — input state in parent re-renders entire tree on every keystroke
function Parent() {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
  return (
    <>
      <SearchInput value={query} onChange={setQuery} />
      <HeavyList items={data} />  {/* re-renders 10x/second while typing */}
    </>
  );
}

// GOOD — SearchInput owns its own state, HeavyList never re-renders while typing
function SearchInput({ onSearch }) {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState(''); // local state
  const debouncedSearch = useCallback(debounce(onSearch, 300), []);
  return <input value={query} onChange={e => {
    setQuery(e.target.value);
    debouncedSearch(e.target.value);
  }} />;
}
```

**Virtualize long lists:**

```jsx
import { FixedSizeList } from 'react-window';

// Only renders ~15 visible rows at any time, regardless of total count
<FixedSizeList height={600} itemCount={10000} itemSize={50} width="100%">
  {({ index, style }) => (
    <div style={style}>{items[index].name}</div>
  )}
</FixedSizeList>
```

**Avoid context for high-frequency updates:**

Context re-renders ALL consumers on every change. Use Zustand with selectors for frequently-changing global state:
```js
// Only re-renders when user.name changes — not on any other store update
const name = useStore(state => state.user.name);
```

**Code-split heavy components:**
```jsx
const HeavyEditor = lazy(() => import('./RichTextEditor'));

{showEditor && (
  <Suspense fallback={<Spinner />}>
    <HeavyEditor />
  </Suspense>
)}
```

