### 7. Debounce & Batch on the Client

**Debounce search:**
```js
// Without debounce: user types "javascript" → 10 API calls
// With debounce: user stops typing → 1 API call after 300ms
const searchAPI = debounce(async (query) => {
  const res = await fetch(`/api/search?q=${encodeURIComponent(query)}`);
  setResults(await res.json());
}, 300);

<input onChange={e => searchAPI(e.target.value)} />
```

**Batch multiple calls into one:**
```js
// BAD — 5 separate API calls on page load (5 round trips)
const [user, orders, notifications, settings, stats] = await Promise.all([
  fetch('/api/user'),
  fetch('/api/orders'),
  fetch('/api/notifications'),
  fetch('/api/settings'),
  fetch('/api/stats'),
]);

// GOOD — 1 API call returns everything the dashboard needs (1 round trip)
const dashboard = await fetch('/api/dashboard/init');
// { user, orders, notifications, settings, stats }
```

