### 8. Database Query Diagnosis Per Endpoint

For every slow endpoint, follow this process:

```js
// Step 1 — Run explain on the slow query
const result = await Model
  .find({ status: 'active', userId: id })
  .explain("executionStats");

/*
  Look at:
  executionTimeMillis  → actual time taken
  totalDocsExamined    → docs scanned (high number = missing index or inefficient query)
  totalKeysExamined    → index keys used
  stage: "COLLSCAN"   → full collection scan — you need an index
  stage: "IXSCAN"     → index used — good
*/

// Step 2 — Add the right index
await Model.collection.createIndex({ status: 1, userId: 1 });
// Compound index on fields used in the query — order matches query selectivity

// Step 3 — Re-run explain and confirm improvement
// totalDocsExamined should drop dramatically
// executionTimeMillis should drop from 500ms to < 5ms
```

