### 9. HTTP/2 and Connection

**HTTP/2 benefits:**
- Multiplexing — multiple requests over one TCP connection (HTTP/1.1 = 6 connections max, one request each)
- Header compression — HPACK reduces repeated headers (saves bandwidth on JSON APIs)
- No head-of-line blocking at HTTP level

Enable in Nginx:
```nginx
listen 443 ssl http2;
```

**Keep-Alive** — reuse existing TCP connection across requests:
```
Connection: keep-alive
Keep-Alive: timeout=5, max=1000
```

