### 11. GraphQL vs REST for Performance

| | REST | GraphQL |
|---|---|---|
| **Over-fetching** | Returns fixed fields — client may get unused data | Client requests exactly the fields it needs |
| **Under-fetching** | Multiple endpoints needed for one page | One query, any nested shape |
| **Caching** | Easy — HTTP GET is cacheable by URL | Harder — all requests POST to `/graphql` |
| **Best for** | Simple CRUD, public APIs, mobile apps needing cache | Complex UIs, mobile (bandwidth-sensitive), internal APIs |

