## 8. Caching Strategy

### Caching Layers (fastest to slowest)

| Layer | Location | Speed | Use For |
|---|---|---|---|
| Browser cache | Client | Fastest | Static assets, API responses with cache headers |
| CDN cache | Edge server near user | Very fast | Public static + semi-static content |
| Redis | App server memory | Fast | DB results, session data, computed values |
| DB query cache | Database | Moderate | Repeated identical queries |
| Disk | Server | Slow | Pre-generated large files |

### Cache Invalidation Strategies

- **TTL-based** — cache expires after fixed time (simple, may serve briefly stale data)
- **Event-based** — invalidate on data change (accurate, more complex)
- **Write-through** — update cache and DB together on write (always fresh, slower writes)
- **Stale-while-revalidate** — serve stale instantly, refresh in background (best UX)

