## 9. Infrastructure & DevOps

### Load Balancing

- Distribute traffic across multiple server instances — no single point of failure
- Strategies: Round Robin, Least Connections, IP Hash (sticky sessions)
- Tools: Nginx, AWS ALB, Cloudflare

### Auto-Scaling

- Horizontal scaling: more instances under load, fewer at night
- AWS: Auto Scaling Groups + ECS / EKS
- Kubernetes: Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA)

### Docker Optimization

```dockerfile
# Order matters — deps layer cached unless package.json changes
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci --only=production
COPY . .

# Multi-stage build
FROM node:20 AS builder
RUN npm ci && npm run build

FROM node:20-alpine       # Alpine: 5MB vs 900MB for full Node image
COPY --from=builder /app/dist ./dist
```

### CI/CD

- Parallelize jobs — test + lint + build simultaneously
- Cache `node_modules` between runs
- Affected test detection — only test changed modules

