## 10. Architecture Level

### Message Queues for Async Processing

```
User clicks "Export PDF"

BAD:  POST /export → server generates PDF (30s) → user waits with spinner
GOOD: POST /export → queues job → returns { jobId, status: "queued" } immediately
      Worker picks up job → generates PDF → notifies via WebSocket
```

Tools: RabbitMQ, Kafka, Bull (Redis-based for Node.js)

### CQRS

- Separate read and write paths — optimize each independently
- Write model: normalized, ACID-safe, slower
- Read model: denormalized, cached, optimized purely for speed

### Circuit Breaker

- If downstream service is failing, stop sending requests — fail fast
- Prevents cascade failures when one service is down
- Library: `opossum` for Node.js

