## 11. Monitoring & Profiling Tools — Explained

### Frontend Tools

| Tool | What it is | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| **Chrome DevTools — Performance tab** | Records a timeline of JS execution, layout recalculations, and paint events. Shows Long Tasks (red blocks) that block the main thread. | When the page feels laggy — find exactly which code is blocking |
| **Chrome DevTools — Memory tab** | Heap snapshots and memory allocation over time. Compare snapshots to find leaks. | When app gets slower the longer you use it — memory leak investigation |
| **Lighthouse** | Automated audit tool built into DevTools. Scores LCP, INP, CLS, TBT, and gives specific recommendations. | Run before and after an optimization to measure improvement objectively |
| **React DevTools Profiler** | Shows flame graph of component render times and render counts. Tells you why each component rendered. | When React UI is slow or re-rendering excessively |
| **why-did-you-render** | npm package that logs to console whenever a component re-renders with same props/state. | When you suspect useless re-renders — it catches them with exact cause |
| **webpack-bundle-analyzer** | Generates an interactive treemap showing every module in your bundle and its size. | When your bundle is too large — reveals which libraries are bloating it |
| **rollup-plugin-visualizer** | Same as bundle-analyzer but for Vite/Rollup. | Vite projects |
| **Squoosh** (squoosh.app) | Browser-based image compressor by Google. Converts to WebP/AVIF, lets you compare quality vs size side by side. | Manually converting and optimizing images before adding to project |
| **WebPageTest** | Tests your page from real browsers in multiple geographic locations. Shows real-world load time and waterfall. | Pre-launch — check how your site performs from India, US, Europe simultaneously |
| **web-vitals** (npm) | Measures Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) in real user browsers, not synthetic testing. | Collect Real User Monitoring (RUM) data in production |

### Backend Tools

| Tool | What it is | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| **clinic.js** | Profiles a running Node.js process. Detects event loop blocking (`clinic doctor`), generates flame graphs (`clinic flame`), and finds memory leaks. | Backend is slow under load — find where time is actually going |
| **0x** | Generates CPU flame graphs from Node.js — shows which functions consume the most CPU time. | High CPU usage — find the hot path |
| **Artillery** | Load testing tool. Simulates thousands of concurrent users and reports p95/p99 latency, error rates. | Before launch — find your breaking point under realistic load |
| **k6** | Modern load testing tool written in Go, scripts in JS. | Same as Artillery — more developer-friendly scripting |

### Database Tools

| Tool | What it is | When to use |
